SOP-008  |  Adding or Updating an API Key
LEARNING OBJECTIVES
By the end of this SOP you will be able to:
Open the .env file safely in Notepad
Add or update an API key using the correct format
Verify the key is working by running the relevant agent
Explain why API keys must never be committed to GitHub


Steps
Open File Explorer and navigate to C:\Projects\FunnyNotFunny\fnf-agents\
Right-click the .env file > Open with > Notepad
Find the line for the key you want to update
Replace the value after the = sign with your new key
Save the file — Ctrl+S
Close Notepad
Open a fresh PowerShell window and test the relevant agent

NOTE: Correct format: KEY_NAME=value-with-no-quotes  — No spaces around =. No quote marks around the value.

PRACTICE EXERCISE  —  API Key Update
